and sweeping prairies.

00:55:34.691 --> 00:55:38.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
Tourists travel from around the world
to see Canada’s moose,

00:55:38.612 --> 00:55:39.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
black bears,

00:55:39.780 --> 00:55:42.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
and woodland caribou.

00:55:42.032 --> 00:55:47.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ll also find one of the world’s
largest deposits of dinosaur fossils.

00:55:47.037 --> 00:55:50.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
And no trip is complete
without trying the local foods.

00:55:50.999 --> 00:55:52.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can have poutine,

00:55:52.960 --> 00:55:55.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
French fries smothered
in gravy and cheese curds,

00:55:55.963 --> 00:55:58.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
or sweets made with maple syrup.

00:55:59.883 --> 00:56:03.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
Canada is unique
in having the world’s longest coastline,

00:56:03.512 --> 00:56:07.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
where our Canadian brothers
have a rich history of preaching.

00:56:08.517 --> 00:56:11.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1930, a motorboat named the <i>Charmian </i>

00:56:11.103 --> 00:56:13.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
and equipped with a powerful speaker system

00:56:13.522 --> 00:56:16.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
was used to project Bible lectures
across the water.

00:56:17.777 --> 00:56:19.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in the 1940’s,

00:56:19.570 --> 00:56:23.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
the <i>Kingdom 1</i> carried ministers up and down
the Newfoundland

00:56:23.532 --> 00:56:25.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Labrador coasts.

00:56:26.118 --> 00:56:28.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that zealous pattern
continues to this day

00:56:28.537 --> 00:56:31.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the fishing towns of Newfoundland,

00:56:31.165 --> 00:56:33.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the lighthouses of Nova Scotia,

00:56:33.543 --> 00:56:35.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
and at the harbors of British Columbia.

00:56:35.753 --> 00:56:37.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
Canada had an all-time high

00:56:37.672 --> 00:56:41.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
